title: Fire is consuming more of the world's forests than ever before, threatening supplies of wood, paper
description: A third of the world's forests are cut for timber. This generates US$1.5 trillion annually. But wildfire threatens industries such as timber milling and paper manufacturing, and the threat is far greater than most people realize.

title: Researcher: Big cats eat more monkeys in a damaged tropical forest, which threatens survival of primate populations
description: Monkeys are not usually a popular menu item for big cats. Primates are, after all, hard to catch: living in the canopies of large trees and rarely coming down to the ground. Jaguar and puma have varied diets and will normally hunt the species that are most common where they live, such as deer, peccary (a type of wild pig) and armadillo.
